            "body": "I'm having a very similar issue.\r\n\r\n**To reproduce:**\r\n\r\n1. `neovide --nofork -- --clean -c 'set cmdheight=0' -c \"=vim.keymap.set('n', '/', 'ms/', { silent = true })\"`\r\n2. Press `/p`\r\n3. Neovide crashes with the (logged) message: `Could not parse event from neovim: invalid u64 format -1`\r\n\r\n**Neovim version**: v0.10.0-dev-735+g8fe9f41f7\r\n**Neovide version**: 0.10.4\r\n\r\nI can't reproduce the original issue though so it doesn't seem to be the exact same bug.",
