            "body": "@bfredl I think this issue should be re-opened. The use case @mawkler reported still sends an invalid event 100% of the time. These are the relevant logs from Neovide\r\n```\r\nERROR [neovide::error_handling] Could not parse event from neovim: invalid event format for event 'grid_cursor_goto' -\r\n [Integer(PosInt(3)), Integer(NegInt(-1)), Integer(PosInt(0))] - invalid u64 format -1\r\nNeovide panicked with the message 'Could not parse event from neovim: invalid event format for event 'grid_cursor_goto\r\n' - [Integer(PosInt(3)), Integer(NegInt(-1)), Integer(PosInt(0))] - invalid u64 format -1'. (File: src/error_handling.\r\n```\r\n\r\nSo, it sends `grid_cursor_goto` with `grid: 2, row: -1, column: 0`, the row is negative, which it shouldn't be.\r\n",
